<li id="cite&#95;note-15"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><a href="#cite_ref-15">↑</a></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Author:James_Henderson&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Author:James Henderson (page does not exist)">Henderson, James</a>, <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=A_History_of_Brazil&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="A History of Brazil (page does not exist)">A History of Brazil</a></i>, London, 1821, pp. 73&#8211;74.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite&#95;note-16"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><a href="#cite_ref-16">↑</a></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="/wiki/Author:Henry_Koster" title="Author:Henry Koster">Koster, Henry</a>, <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Travels_in_Brazil&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Travels in Brazil (page does not exist)">Travels in Brazil</a></i>, second edition, in two volumes, vol. II, London, 1817, pp. 247&#8211;259.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite&#95;note-17"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><a href="#cite_ref-17">↑</a></span> <span class="reference-text">Christie, pp. 69&#8211;76.</span>
